@section Utilities for sorted lists


@defun sorted-list-insert @var{item} @var{list} @var{item>}
Build a new list holding the same arguments of @var{list}, a list sorted
in increasing order, and @var{item} inserted in such a position that the
order is preserved.  The returned list may share structure with
@var{list}.

@var{item>} must be a predicate accepting two arguments and returning
true if the first is greater than the second.

If @var{item} is equal to one of the items in @var{list}: @var{item} is
added before the item from @var{list}.
@end defun


@defun sorted-list-insert/uniq @var{item} @var{list} @var{item<} @var{item>}
Like @func{sorted-list-insert}, buth if @var{item} is equal to one of
the items in @var{list}: @var{item} is discarded, and @var{list} it self
is returned.
@end defun


@defun union-of-sorted-lists @var{list1} @var{list2} @var{item<} @var{item>}
Build a new list representing the union of the lists arguments.
@var{list1} and @var{list2} are interpreted as lists sorted in
increasing order, and the result of the union is a sorted list.  The
returned list may share structure with the list arguments.

@var{item<} and @var{item>} must be predicates accepting two arguments
and returning true if the first is less than/greater than the second.

When both @var{item<} and @var{item>} return @false{}, the two items are
considered equal; in this case all the equal items are added to the
result, in such a way that the items from @var{list1} all come before
the items from @var{list2}.
@end defun


@defun union-of-sorted-lists/uniq @var{list1} @var{list2} @var{item<} @var{item>}
Like @func{union-of-sorted-lists}, but when equal items are found only
the ones from @var{list1} are added to the result.  Examples:

@example
(union-of-sorted-lists/uniq
  '(0 1   3     8 9 10)
  '(  1 2   4 5        11 23)
  < >)
@result{} '(0 1 2 3 4 5 8 9 10 11 23)
;;     ^
;; from list1

(union-of-sorted-lists/uniq
  '(0 1 1   3)
  '(  1   2   4)
  < >)
@result{} '(0 1 1 2 3 4 5)
;;     ^ ^
;; both from list1
@end example
@end defun

