@section Multimethod dispatching


@dfn{Generic functions} are procedures that can be specialised to the
(conventional) record types of their arguments.  Each specialisation of
a generic function is called @dfn{method}.  When applying a generic
function to a set of arguments, the most specific method with respect to
the arguments' types is chosen.

@menu
