Raised to signal an expression/pattern mismatch while evaluating the
expansion of @func{match}; it is derived from @samp{&mismatch}.  There
is only one field, @samp{expression}, which holds the mismatched
expression.
@end deftp


@defun make-match-mismatch @var{expression}
Build and return a condition of type @samp{&match-mismatch}.
@end defun


@defun match-mismatch? @var{obj}
Return @true{} if @var{obj} is a condition of type
@samp{&match-mismatch}.
@end defun


@defun match-mismatch-expression @var{obj}
Accessor for the @samp{expression} field of a @samp{&match-mismatch}
